  1.30.0

  â— Add [38;5;230mStandard::PluginSupport[39m module of classes designed to make it a little
  easier to author plugins. [38;5;230mMergesUpstreamMetadata#merge[39m will allow a minimal
  YAML config (say, [38;5;230mstandard-sorbet[39mâ€™s, which only contains [38;5;230mEnabled[39m values for
  each rule) to merge in any other defaults from a source YAML (e.g.[38;5;230mrubocop-sorbet[39mâ€™s which includes [38;5;230mDescription[39m, [38;5;230mVersionAdded[39m, and so on).
  This way that metadata is neither absent at runtime nor duplicated in a standard
  plugin that mirrors a rubocop extension

