  1.28.0

  â— Refactor Standard into 3 gems and convert all built-in configuration intolint_roller Â» https://github.com/standardrb/lint_roller plugins. See:
    â— standard-performance Â» https://github.com/standardrb/standard-performance
    â— standard-custom Â» https://github.com/standardrb/standard-custom
  â— Standardâ€™s behavior when merging multiple [38;5;230mextend_config[39m that change the same
  set of rules has been fixed to be first-in-wins, as opposed to last-in-wins.
  This ensures a consistent behavior across plugins and extended configurations,
  namely that the first thing to configure a given rule effectively locks it
  from subsequent changes
  â— Enable [38;5;230mDisabledByDefault: true[39m. This shouldnâ€™t impact anyone, but might
  change the behavior of some [38;5;230mextend_config[39m users. Because Standard specifies
  every rule in rubocop and rubocop-performance, this configurationâ€™s absence
  wasnâ€™t felt until we went to the plugin system, where it makes much more sense
  for plugins to opt-in to the cops they want to configure, as opposed to just
  running every single one that they happen to load/require

